# SlugBase

A bookmark manager with built-in URL shortening and keyboard-driven launcher — save bookmarks, assign short slugs, and jump to any URL from the address bar or command palette (`/go/<slug>`). Deployed as a managed hosted service and a self-hosted install from one codebase.

## Tech stack (settled — spec §19, decisions #37–#50)

- **Single repo:** pnpm workspace monorepo with **Turborepo** task pipelines (spec §2.2, §19)
- **Language:** **TypeScript** (strict, no `any`) everywhere (spec §19, decision #37)
- **Backend:** **NestJS** — its DI/module system hosts the config-selected external interfaces (no deployment-mode branching) and generates OpenAPI; runs as a Node container on Fly.io — spec §19, §2.6, §11, §14.7
- **Web client:** **React Router v7** (framework mode) — same app runs on Cloudflare Workers (hosted) and as Node inside the self-host image — spec §19, §14.7
- **Marketing:** **Astro** (static, zero-JS-by-default) on Cloudflare Workers — spec §2.3, §19
- **Persistence:** **Drizzle ORM** + **Drizzle Kit** behind the data-access abstraction; **PostgreSQL** generates migrations and powers runtime (hosted Neon `aws-eu-central-1` + self-host Postgres). Embedded SQLite self-host is **deferred** (Fast-Follow) — spec §11.9, §16, decisions #32/#41
- **Contracts/validation:** **Zod** + **ts-rest** in `shared-types`; generates the OpenAPI description — spec §18, §19
- **UI:** **Tailwind** (token-bridged to `colors_and_type.css`) + **Radix** primitives + **cmdk** palette — spec §23, rule `11-design-system`
- **Tests:** **Vitest** + **Supertest** (unit/integration) + **Playwright** (e2e) — spec §22.4
- **Packages:** `backend` · `web` · `marketing` · `shared-types` · `ui` · `docs` (spec §19)
- **Auth:** server-side sessions (DB-backed, no JWT access/refresh); TOTP MFA (otplib); OIDC/SSO; **argon2id** password hashing; double-submit CSRF — spec §5
- **Billing:** Stripe (hosted); no-op billing (self-hosted) — spec §11.4
- **AI:** **OpenAI** behind the vendor-neutral AI interface — spec §11.2, decision #49
- **i18n:** English + German at launch; repo-JSON catalogs + react-i18next (web) / native `t()` (marketing) — spec §17
- **Secrets:** **Infisical** (Infisical Cloud EU — `https://eu.infisical.com`, project `slugbase-cloud`, envs `dev` / `staging` / `prod`); `infisical run --env=dev -- <command>` locally — decision #34
- **Bot protection:** Cloudflare Turnstile (hosted default); no-op (self-hosted) — spec §11.8

### Hosted infrastructure (settled — spec §14.7, decisions #31–32)

| Layer | Platform | Region |
|---|---|---|
| Web client | **Cloudflare Workers** | Global edge |
| API / back-end | **Fly.io** (`fra`) | Frankfurt, DE |
| Database | **Neon Postgres** (`aws-eu-central-1`) | Frankfurt, DE |
| Marketing site | **Cloudflare Workers** | Global edge; separately built |

**App naming** (Fly.io apps + CF Worker scripts): `slugbase-<env>-<app>`, `<env>` ∈ {`staging`, `production`}, `<app>` ∈ {`api`, `web`, `marketing`} — e.g. `slugbase-staging-api`, `slugbase-production-web`. No `development` deployment (local dev only). Platform identifiers, not public hostnames — spec §14.7, decision #51.

Self-hosted: **combined container image**, single port, operator's own infrastructure — spec §14.2.

### CI/CD (settled — spec §22, decision #35)

Single workflow file: `.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml`. **GitHub-hosted runners** (`ubuntu-latest`). Branches: `staging` and `main`.
Secrets via Infisical OIDC (`Infisical/secrets-action`) — only `INFISICAL_DOMAIN` and `INFISICAL_OIDC_IDENTITY_ID` live in GHA secrets.
Stages: CI checks → staging deploy (push `staging`) → prepare release (push `main`) → production deploy (release published) → GHCR self-hosted image push.

## Repository state

This repo currently contains only docs. Application code is built phase-by-phase from `docs/internal/slugbase-development-roadmap.md` (plan file — **DRAFT, pre-GitHub**; phases P1–P6). When unsure what phase we're in, read the roadmap.

## Spec doc precedence (when docs conflict)

1. `docs/internal/slugbase-mvp-spec.md` — **product source of truth**: product vision, architecture, data model, interface contracts, billing, security, self-hosted story, resolved decisions
2. `docs/internal/engineering-decisions.md` — **engineering source of truth**: stack, tooling, conventions, infra, CI commands. `docs/internal/defaults-and-constants.md` holds pinned config values. The spec (1) wins on product conflicts.
3. `docs/internal/design-prototype/V1/` — **visual & interaction-design source of truth** (design tokens, screens, states, copy tone). On any product conflict, the spec (1) wins — see spec §23.4 and rule `11-design-system.mdc`.

*(Companion docs: `engineering-decisions.md`, `defaults-and-constants.md`, `slugbase-development-roadmap.md` (phased plan). `schema-reference.md` / `api-design.md` grow incrementally with the roadmap.)*

## Hard rules

- If a behaviour is not defined in a spec doc, **ask before guessing**.
- Never invent fields, endpoints, flows, or plans not present in the spec.
- **"Workspace"** is the only tenant term — "organization" is deprecated (spec §3, decision #1).
- **"Folder"** is the only container term — no "collection" (spec §3, decision #2).
- **"Pinning"** is the only prominence mechanism — no "favorites" anywhere (spec §3, decision #3).
- Bookmark editing is modal-only — no dedicated detail route (spec §6.2, decision #19).
- Slugs are private to a workspace — no anonymous `/go` resolution in v1 (spec §8.2, decision #23).
- All user-facing strings must be i18n keys — no hardcoded English or German (spec §17). Never copy the prototype's hard-coded English strings.
- UI follows the V1 design prototype + tokens (`docs/internal/design-prototype/V1/`, spec §23); paid tier is **"Personal"** not "Pro"; Free cap is **50**; no folder cap; API tokens not plan-gated (spec §23.4).
- Single repo, no submodules, pnpm throughout — no npm or yarn lockfiles (spec §2.2).
- Self-hosted and cloud are the **same code path** — no `isCloud`/deployment-mode branches in app logic (spec §1, §15).
